There is Internet stuff saying that foxes are close enough to dogs, biochemically and metabolically speaking, that the same foods that are poisonous for dogs are also poisonous for foxes, though the relative rarity of pet foxes means there hasn't been a lot of research done. There are chemicals in chocolate that are pretty toxic to most mammals other than primates. But I like to think that anthro canids wouldn't be in deadly danger from eating raisins or chocolate or garlic, they just might get an upset stomach or what some in my family euphemistically call "distress of the lower tract" instead of dying slowly and horribly of kidney failure. And it may be a matter of concentrations. Lots of spices contain irritant plant toxins. The chemical that gives cinnamon its distinctive odor and "bite" will give you chemical burns if it gets on your skin, if it's pure enough.
